cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1) cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on building language models for code-switched text using recurrent neural networks. 
2) cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel recurrent neural network unit and pretraining technique to improve the language models. 
3) cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses generative models to pretrain the language models. 
4) cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses recurrent neural networks for the language models. 
5) cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on sound or audio data, but it is still possible as code-switching can also occur in spoken language.
